title: Bug 4121: JarExporter causes out-of-sync issue
OB: When exporting a directory (project) and placing the exported JAR in the same directory (project), an out-of-sync message occurs when overwriting the exported JAR file for the second time.
EB: The exported JAR file should be overwritten in the same directory without triggering an out-of-sync message.
SR:
1. Export a directory (project) to create a JAR file.
2. Place the exported JAR in the same directory (project).
3. Overwrite the exported JAR file for the second time.
Result: Observe the out-of-sync message.
